'Benzoic acid' (), C 7H 6O 2 (or
C 6H 5COOH), is a colorless crystalline solid and a simple
aromatic carboxylic acid. The name derived from gum benzoin, which was for a
long time the only source for benzoic acid. Its salts are used as a food
preservative and benzoic acid is an important precursor for the synthesis of
many other organic substances. The salts and esters of benzoic acid are known as
'benzoates' ().
